  <description>

<![CDATA[

  <p>

  This project provides an integration of the bigdata&#174; RDF database layer
  for Sesame 1.x.

  </p><p>

  SAIL is an acroynm for Storage And Inference Layer.  Sesame 1.x
  defines two SAIL interfaces: <dl>

  <dt>RdfRepository</dt><dd>The basic triple store API.</dd>

  <dt>RdfSchemaRepository</dt><dd>An extended interface that requires
  support for RDFS truth maintenance.</dd>

  </dl>

  Implementations of both SAILs are contained in this project.  In
  addition, there is an option to turn on RDF(S)+ truth maintenance
  for the RdfRepository and an option to turn on owl:sameAs,
  owl:equivalentClass, and owl:equivalentProperty entailments.

  </p><p>

  Performance for bigdata and its RDF database layer are very good -
  you can load data into the triple store at rates exceeding 20,000
  triples per second on any reasonable computer.  The algorithms for
  forward closure likewise exhibit high performance and loading with
  incremental truth maintenance demonstrates throughput in the range
  of 15,000 triples per second.  However, the Sesame 1.x platform does
  not make it possible to optimize high-level queries for the backend
  database and high-level queries will suffer as a result.  Therefore
  a Sesame 2.x integration is in the works.  This will be a native
  quad store.

  </p>

]]>

  </description>

